    <string name="instructions_section1_title">What is Hourglass ?</string>
    <string name="instructions_section1_description">"Hourglass is a virtual version of a popular classic game which is known in many countries around the world. It is also known as:
Celebrities, The Hat Game, Lunchbox, Fish Bowl, Salad Bowl, Who Is The Man &amp; The Name Game.

You will need at least 4 people to play and the more the merrier!

Get together in a video call and play through rounds of: <b>Describe, One Word &amp; Charades</b>."
    </string>

    <string name="instructions_section2_title">Instructions</string>
    <string name="instructions_section2_subtitle_setup">Setup</string>
    <string name="instructions_section2_description">"1. One person creates a game and shares it with others.
2. Each player writes their words on ‚Äúcards‚Äù that will be guessed later. All cards from all players are gathered together in one deck.
3. Each player chooses their team. "</string>
    <string name="instructions_section2_subtitle_game">Gameplay</string>
    <string name="instructions_section2_description2">"Each team tries to guess as many cards as possible against the clock (aka Hourglass).
In each turn one player is giving the clues while the rest of their team guesses.

One game includes 3 rounds and the same cards are reused in every round!
</string>

    <string name="instructions_section3_title">The rounds</string>
    <string name="instructions_section3_round1_title">Round 1 : Describe</string>
    <string name="instructions_section3_round2_title">Round 2 : One Word</string>
    <string name="instructions_section3_round3_title">Round 3 : Charades</string>
    <string name="instructions_section3_round1_descriptions">You can use as many words as you like to describe the word on the card, without acting or gestures.</string>
    <string name="instructions_section3_round2_descriptions">You can say exactly 1 word per card. Once you said a word, you can only repeat it‚Ä¶</string>
    <string name="instructions_section3_round3_descriptions">Act and use mime to communicate the card. No words or sounds allowed‚Ä¶</string>
    <string name="instructions_section3_general_description"><b>The scores from all three rounds are added together. The team with the most points wins!</b></string>

